                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>1 papyrus ; 13.8 x 38.1 cm</support>
                        <condition>
                           <ab type="conservation">Complete except from the top left corner. Many holes at all the fragment preserved</ab>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">recto: 24 lines;verso: 1 line</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Source of description: recto-verso</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <p>Three hands: Hand 1: lines 1-19: cursive handwriting, experient, with many ligatures (same hand as Hand 1 in P.Mich. inv. 79). Hand 2: lines 20-29; larger letters and upright formed. Hand 3: lines 30-32 more cursive. A horizontal stroke has ben drawn below the last line of each hand. The document had been invalidated by crossed strokes</p>
